===Etymology===
[[hand]] + Old French ''covrechef'' (literally, "cover-head")

===Noun===
'''hankerchief''' (''plural'' '''handkerchieves'''; ''colloquial short form'' '''[[hanky]]''')

#A piece of [[cloth]], usually square and often fine and elegant, carried for wiping the face, nose or hands.
#A piece of cloth shaped like a handkerchief to be worn about the neck; a [[neckerchief]] or [[neckcloth]].

